name: Ext.chart.Caption
doc: Chart captions can be used to place titles, subtitles, credits and other captions inside a chart. Please see the chart's Ext.chart.AbstractChart.captions config documentation for the general description of the way captions work, and refer to the documentation of this class' configs for details.

members.name: align
members.doc: Determines the horizontal alignment of the caption's text.
members.short_doc: Determines the horizontal alignment of the caption's text. ...

members.name: alignTo
members.doc: Whether to align the caption to the 'series' (default) or the 'chart'.
members.short_doc: Whether to align the caption to the 'series' (default) or the 'chart'. ...

members.name: debug
members.doc: Whether to show the bounding boxes or not.
members.short_doc: Whether to show the bounding boxes or not. ...

members.name: docked
members.doc: The position of the caption in a chart.
members.short_doc: The position of the caption in a chart. ...

members.name: hidden
members.short_doc: Controls the visibility of the caption. ...

members.name: padding
members.doc: The uniform padding applied to both top and bottom of the caption's text.
members.short_doc: The uniform padding applied to both top and bottom of the caption's text. ...

members.name: rect
members.doc: The logical rect of the caption in the surfaceName surface.

members.name: sprite
members.doc: The text sprite used to render caption's text.
members.short_doc: The text sprite used to render caption's text. ...

members.name: style
members.doc: Style attributes for the caption's text. All attributes that are valid text sprite attributes are valid here. However, only font attributes (such as fontSize, fontFamily, ...), color attributes (such as fillStyle) and textAlign attribute are guaranteed to produce correct behavior. For example, transform attributes are not officially supported.
members.short_doc: Style attributes for the caption's text. ...

members.name: text
members.doc:
The text displayed by the caption. Multi-line captions are allowed, e.g.:

captions: {
    title: {
        text: 'India\'s tiger population\n'
            + 'from 1970 to 2015'
    }
}
members.short_doc: The text displayed by the caption. ...

members.name: weight
members.doc: The weight controls the order in which the captions are created. Captions with lower weights are created first. This affects chart's layout. For example, if two captions are docked to the 'top', the one with the lower weight will end up on top of the other.
members.short_doc: The weight controls the order in which the captions are created. ...

members.name: computeRect
members.doc: Computes and sets the caption's rect. Shrinks the given chart rect to accomodate the caption. The chart rect is [top, left, width, height] in chart's body element coordinates. The shrink rect is {left, top, right, bottom} in caption surface coordinates.
members.short_doc: Computes and sets the caption's rect. ...
